For locally connected toposes there is an easy condition on sites
equivalent to connectedness. What about the general case? Moreover, I
would be interested in a condition on sites equivalent to all maps
from \Omega to \Delta(2) being constant.
The reason for the question is quite specific. If one takes presheaves
over the monoid Sp(2^N,2^N) of continuous endomaps of Cantor space 2^N
it is straightforward to observe that \Pi(\Omega) \cong 1. I wonder
whether this remains so when taking sheaves w.r.t. the topology
generated by finite (disjoint) open covers.

Thomas Streicher


